The paper deals with auction theory and learning bidders' valuation distributions, which are topics that fall under game theory (cs.GT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of observations and the goal of recovering the underlying bid distributions suggest that the paper may also be relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data science (cs.DS). Finally, the mention of common-value components added to private values suggests that the paper may also be relevant to information theory (cs.IT).
